transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling customer service. I can help you.

Speaker 2: Yes. Good afternoon. I was calling because I ordered the pills back in November.

Speaker 1: And I still have not received anything that you charged me for it.

Speaker 2: I paid $65 and I haven't received anything. $63.95.

Speaker 1: Back in November 7th. And I haven't received anything.

Speaker 2: Okay. Can I have your name and birthday?

Speaker 1: Okay. My name is Roque. R-O-Q-U-E. N-C-N-E-S-E-N-C-I-N-I-A-S.

Speaker 2: That was November 7th.

Speaker 1: Okay. It looks like the doctor had wanted you to do a video and you didn't do the video.

Speaker 2: So I'm going to have the doctor give you a phone call so we can get this medication out to you, okay?

Speaker 1: So you're going to send him a medication you sent?

Speaker 2: Yeah. The doctor has to write the prescription. But I'm going to have the doctor give you a phone call.

Speaker 1: Is this a good phone number?

Speaker 2: Yeah. This is the phone number. Yes.

Speaker 1: Now, how many of those pills were they? I can't remember the amount.

Speaker 2: It was 10.

Speaker 1: How many?

Speaker 2: 10.

Speaker 1: 10?

Speaker 2: Uh-huh.

Speaker 1: For $63?

Speaker 2: $63?

Speaker 1: That's correct. Is this a good phone number?

Speaker 2: Yes. This is 505-603-2526.

Speaker 1: Perfect. Alrighty.

Speaker 2: Okay. I'm going to have the doctor give you a phone call, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay. Now, when will that be? Today? Tomorrow?

Speaker 2: Today. It'll be tomorrow because it's kind of late already today.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Alrighty. Have a wonderful day.

Speaker 1: Thank you.
